## Implementation Plan: `@prisma/rest-api-client-generator`

### Architectural Overview

The package follows the exact same structural conventions as `@prisma/client-generator-js` and `@prisma/client-generator-ts`. It uses `esbuild` via the shared `helpers/compile/build.ts` + `adapterConfig` pipeline to produce dual CJS/ESM bundles at `dist/index.js` and `dist/index.mjs`. The generator class implements `Generator` from `@prisma/generator`, reads the DMMF from `GeneratorOptions`, then calls a pure orchestration function that builds in-memory strings and flushes them to the output directory using Node's `fs/promises`.

